snippet.textDisplay:
In 1975, the iconic Iranian singer Googoosh (Faegheh Atashin) visited Afghanistan and performed at Ghazi Stadium. Afghan audiences adored her. During her visit, musician Farid Zaland gave her the song “Man Amade’am” (“I’ve Arrived”), which was composed by his father, the late Afghan poet, singer, and composer Ustad Jalil Zaland.

Googoosh later released the song on her 1975 album “Pol”. It became an international hit, loved by millions to this day.
